						<summary>

						<p>On the west wall of the central shrine, Śivayōganāthasvāmi temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Year 9 = 980 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>Records some provision made by a merchant by name Subrahmaṇyaṉ of Kīḻmāndūr residing at Tiruviśalūr for burning a perpetual lamp to the god Perumāṉaḍigaḷ at Tiruviśalūr in Amaṉinārāyaṇa-chchaturvēdimaṅgalam, a <hi rend="italic">dēvadānam-brahmadēyam,</hi> with an <hi rend="italic">uḻakku</hi> of ghee everyday. The temple officials <hi rend="italic">(śrī-kāriyam śeyvār)</hi> and <hi rend="italic">peruṅguṟi-perumakkaḷ</hi> undertook to maintain this charity.</p>						

						<p>Published in <hi rend="italic">S.I.I.,</hi> Vol. XIX No. 221. </p>						

						</summary>
